Detailed Description

Barycentric Polynomial Interpolation where the given sample points are chebyshev nodes of the second kind.

This algorithm neither supports differentiation nor integration.

) [static]

Generate a set of chebyshev points of the second kind in the interval [a,b]. These are the expected points t for the values v(t) to be provided in Init.

Parameters:
a Left bound of the interval.
b Right bound of the interval.
numberOfPoints Number of sample nodes to generate.
Returns:
Chebyshev points (second kind) in the interval [a,b], i.e. 0.5*(b+a) + 0.5*(b-a)*cos(Pi*i/n)
